<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>They went through a sticky patch in their marriage a couple of years ago.</p>

<p>But it seems that Jennie Garth and Dave Abrams have their relationship back on track as the couple enjoyed a shopping trip together on Tuesday in LA.</p>

<p>The two were snapped leaving a store in Pasadena, California, after picking up some purchases.</p>

<p>Shop till you drop: Jennie Garth and husband Dave Abrams were spotted leaving a store in Pasadena, California, on Tuesday as they enjoyed a retail outing together</p>

<p>Garth, who found fame as Kelly on Beverly Hills, 90210, was dressed in a long gray shirt left loose over black cycling shorts and stepped out in black sneakers.</p>

<p>The actress wore her blonde hair tied back from her face and she sported spectacles and a purple cloth face mask.</p>

<p>Abrams, 39, an actor, wore a black t-shirt and shorts with black and white trainers. </p>

<p>He had on a green peaked cap, black-framed spectacles and knotted a bandana around his face as a covering.</p>

<p>Celebrity: The Beverly Hills, 90210 alum was dressed in a gray shirt left loose over black cycling shorts and stepped out in black sneakers. She wore spectacles and a purple face mask</p>

<p>Garth and Abrams began dating in fall 2014  following the actress' divorce from second husband Peter Facinelli the previous year. </p>

<p>They became engaged in April 2015 and exchanged vows in July that year.  </p>

<p>However, they separated in 2017 and in April 2018 they filed for divorce. But then in February 2019, they got back together and had the divorce proceedings dismissed.</p>

<p>In an interview with People, Gary had explained: 'Dave and I fell in love really fast and got married within six months,' Garth said. 'We rushed it too much, and that hurt us.'</p>

<p>Rocky road: Garth and Abrams, pictured in November 2019, married in 2015 after a few months of dating. They split in 2017 and planned to divorce but then reconciled last year</p>

<p>Garth, who was married to first husband, musician Daniel B. Clark from 1994 to 1996, told the publication that the thought of going through a third divorce 'really devastated me.' </p>

<p>She told People: 'We definitely had to just part ways completely. And just when I felt whole again, we started hanging out. He needed to go away and figure everything out.' </p>

<p>She added: 'Marriage is not like a fairy tale. It's a process, and it's about continuously wanting to make it better.'</p>

<p>90s star: Garth found fame as Kelly on Beverly Hills, 90210. She was previously married to musician  Daniel B. Clark from 1994 to 1996 and Peter Facinelli from 2001 to 2013 </p>
